<li id="cite_note-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-13">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFPeele2016" class="citation journal">Peele S (December 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S235285321630013X">"People Control Their Addictions: No matter how much the "chronic" brain disease model of addiction indicates otherwise, we know that people can quit addictions - with special reference to harm reduction and mindfulness"</a>. <i>Addictive Behaviors Reports</i>. <b>4</b>: 97–101. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.abrep.2016.05.003">10.1016/j.abrep.2016.05.003</a>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5836519">5836519</a></span>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29511729">29511729</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Addictive+Behaviors+Reports&amp;rft.atitle=People+Control+Their+Addictions%3A+No+matter+how+much+the+%22chronic%22+brain+disease+model+of+addiction+indicates+otherwise%2C+we+know+that+people+can+quit+addictions+-+with+special+reference+to+harm+reduction+and+mindfulness&amp;rft.volume=4&amp;rft.pages=97-101&amp;rft.date=2016-12&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5836519&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F29511729&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.abrep.2016.05.003&amp;rft.aulast=Peele&amp;rft.aufi