<li id="cite_note-Chromatin_states-104"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Drug_addiction#cite_ref-Chromatin_states_104-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWalkerCatesHellerNestler2015" class="citation journal">Walker DM, Cates HM, Heller EA, Nestler EJ (February 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4293340">"Regulation of chromatin states by drugs of abuse"</a>. <i>Curr. Opin. Neurobiol</i>. <b>30</b>: 112–21. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.conb.2014.11.002">10.1016/j.conb.2014.11.002</a>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PMC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMC (identifier)">PMC</a>&#160;<span class="cs1-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4293340">4293340</a></span>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25486626">25486626</a>. <q>Studies investigating general HDAC inhibition on behavioral outcomes have produced varying results but it seem